Suggest Paperless-ngx metadata from OCR text. OCR may contain errors.

Return valid JSON only, without Markdown:
{
  "title": "",
  "tags": [],
  "correspondent": "",
  "document_type": "",
  "created_date": ""
}

Fill only requested keys. Return an empty string or empty array for unrequested or unknown values.

Requested fields:
- title: {{.GenerateTitles}}
- tags: {{.GenerateTags}}
- correspondent: {{.GenerateCorrespondents}}
- document_type: {{.GenerateDocumentTypes}}
- created_date: {{.GenerateCreatedDate}}

Rules:
- Language is likely {{.Language}}.
- title: follow `{{.TitleSchema}}` when clear. Use a full sender name, broad document kind, reference, and concise subject. Do not prefix dates. Avoid repeating domains already captured by tags or document_type.
- tags: prefer existing taxonomy tags; keep existing non-workflow tags unless clearly wrong; suggest new tags only when no existing tag fits.
- correspondent: prefer exact or normalized existing names; obey the blacklist; suggest a new name only when none fits.
- document_type: prefer existing types; suggest new types only when broad and reusable. Do not create types from sender, customer, product, reference, subject, or list/overview wording.
- created_date: return YYYY-MM-DD. If only month/year is known, use day 01. If only year is known, use January 01. If no date is found, use {{.Today}}.

